# Run the project text-lint before every git commit.
# Catches the "Simplified Chinese leaked into a non-allowlisted file" class
# of bug that otherwise only surfaces at `pnpm dist:dev` time — too late,
# after the branch has already been pushed and someone else picks up the
# lint hit during a merge.
#
# scripts/check-chinese-comments.js scans `git ls-files` directly, so it
# catches violations in modified files plus newly tracked / staged files.
# Runtime is < 1s on the current repo size, well below a noticeable commit
# pause.
#
# To bypass in a genuine emergency (rare — the lint allowlist already
# covers locale dictionaries, project instruction docs, and three test
# files that legitimately quote zh-CN), use:
#   git commit --no-verify
# Only use --no-verify when you have already audited the diff and know the
# Chinese text is in an allowlisted file; the same lint runs at every
# `pnpm dist:dev` and will block daily-build CI if violations slip through.

pnpm lint:comments
